title: Gisele Bundchen resumes her daily workout routine in Miami after Hurricane Milton pummeled Florida
text:
By Alesia Stanford For Dailymail.Com
Published: 00:16 BST, 12 October 2024 | Updated: 00:23 BST, 12 October 2024
Gisele Bündchen seemed to get back to her regular routine Friday, after laying low following the havoc Hurricane Milton created across the state of Florida.
The model,44, who recently posed in a sexy photo shoot in her native Brazil, appeared to wave at a friend as she returned from her morning coffee run in Miami.
The city was not affected by the massive hurricane as much as the rest of the state, and many Floridians forced to evacuate their homes took refuge from the storm there.
The cover model looked relaxed in a gray sweatshirt with a pair of tight fitting black leggings.
She stepped out in a pair of black flip flops and carried a taupe bag.
Gisele Bündchen seemed to get back to her regular routine after laying low following the havoc Hurricane Milton created across the state of Florida, and appeared to be returning from a coffee run Friday morning in Miami
Her golden blonde hair was brushed in loose waves and she appeared to be makeup free.
A while later, the leggy beauty was spotted wearing a pair of black workout shorts with black T-shirt as she headed for her workout.
The Nourish author wore a pair of beige flip flops and placed a beige billed hat over her long locks.
She carried a white water bottle and a brown shoulder bag.
Bündchen incorporates a variety of practices into her workout routine including kayaking, yoga, strength training and jiu-jitsu, according to a 2023 interview with Women’s Health.
Walking her dog is a favorite for of exercise for her and her pooch. ‘Walking is underestimated,’ she told the publication. ‘That’s great for me and great for him.’
It was jiu-jitsu that eventually introduced the model to her current boyfriend, Joaquim Valente, owns a jiujitsu studio with his brothers Pedro and Gui Valente in Miami.
They started dating in June 2023, after first meeting in December 2021 when she sought out jiu-jitsu training for her son and then decided to take classes too.

”Initially, I wasn’t even considering it for myself. But when I brought [her son Benjamin, now 14] to the first class and started talking to Joaquim, I realized that it was much more than self defense,’ she told Dust magazine.
‘I have a friend who told me about the Valente brothers and their martial art school, and since I wanted to steer my almost teenage son in the right direction, I thought he might be interested in this.”
The athletic beauty has also learned to appreciate the mental growth that comes from her practice, revealing it’s made her a better listener, and helped her relax.
Bündchen shares her son, and daughter Vivian, who will turn 12 in December with her ex-husband, former NFL great Tom Brady, 47.
